      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KIWI JENNI (10) resumes, now with the Maher yard having run second on debut at Hamilton under Shane Jackson. That was a great run back in November when charging to the line and the 1525m here fresh should be ideal. She's got good upside and will be very hard to hold out. SOLDIER BOI (5) resumes having hit the line well here on debut behind Storm Leopard who has gone on to win at Group 2 level. He likely gets back but looks a nice staying type going forward and will be charging late. LE PLUS RAPIDE (1) battled on well for second at Terang when last seen on wet ground and should be nice and fit with each way claims. TARNATION (6) is a gelding by Almanzor on debut who could surprise while HIGH ALTITUDE (7) is going okay and is in the minor mix.",
